Title : Abrams Creek (Tennessee)
Text : [[File:Abrams Creek Near Trailhead.JPG|thumb|Abrams Creek]]
'''Abrams Creek''' is a [[Stream|creek]] in [[Blount County, Tennessee|Blount County]], [[Tennessee]].  Its headwaters are in [[Cades Cove]], and it is a tributary of the [[Little Tennessee River]].<ref name=peine/><ref name=rozema>{{cite book|author=Vicki Rozema|title=Footsteps of the Cherokees, 2nd ed.|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=gfic5eOnNDwC&pg=PA171|year=2007|publisher=John F. Blair|isbn=978-0-89587-421-4|page=171}}</ref> It is named after the [[Chilhowee (Cherokee town)|Chilhowee]] [[Cherokee]] chief Old Abraham ("Abram").<ref name=rozema/>  Visitors swim and fish in the creek.<ref>{{cite book|author=Margaret Littman|title=Moon Tennessee|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ueryAAAAQBAJ&pg=PA411|date=19 March 2013|publisher=Avalon Travel|isbn=978-1-61238-150-3|page=411}}</ref>  The creek was deliberately poisoned in 1957 to kill fish in potential competition with [[rainbow trout]]; many fish species were extirpated from the river and have never recovered.<ref name=peine>{{cite book|author1=John Peine|author2=Samab Foundation|title=Ecosystem Management for Sustainability: Principles and Practices Illustrated by a Regional Biosphere Reserve Cooperative|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=PElLQwiWFK4C&pg=PA50|year=1998|publisher=CRC Press|isbn=978-1-57444-053-9|page=50}}</ref>

